<br>
I'm not trying to argue for realisim.  The whole idea of No Drop is just a retarded one.<br>
<br>
I'm going to take an RP stance here.  I'm also going to use other games as examples.<br>
<br>
Someone picks up this game.  For some very, unknown reason they decide they want to make cash or &quot;RP&quot; a merchant.(I hate buying and selling things, takes too much time)  Now they get into the game and start playing.  They finally make enough money to buy something, then they sell that for more profit.  Wow, feels good to finally be making money.  Now they come up with their sometimes good sometimes bad extremlly long sentances about the goods they are selling.  A couple weeks go by and they have made a good bit of plat.  But now, they are starting to realize that anything worth buying or selling is No Drop and can't get their hands on it.  Yet, they don't enjoy the hack and slash part of the game.  What option do they have no?  Where is the fun in the game for them?  <br>
<br>
Now, if you look at SWG, I think they realized this stance.  Because there is absolutely no No Drop from what I've seen so far.  The game is based soley on player economy, the best &quot;class&quot; to be if you want good things is a crafter.  You then SELL this stuff like you are a merchant. <br>
<br>
So, what I'm saying.  Is no drop limits this game to nothing but a hack and slash game.  So much for an RP server =P  <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.moneepennee.net/halman/images/SinnajiSig.png" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><br>
