<br>
First off, SOE defines exploit as &quot;Working around or bypassing the intended workings of the game&quot;. So let's list some exploits and then all look in the mirror:<br>
<br>
*  Multi-Questing<br>
*  Raiding to beat TLC code<br>
*  Grandmaster Carry-Alls<br>
*  Trapping mobs in the scenery<br>
*  Fearkiting into a wall<br>
*  Luring the Emperor out of his room<br>
*  Passing no-drop items via a bag on the floor drop<br>
<br>
SOE tends to work on a major/mino exploit type of system. The ones they deem minor they tend to ignore. The major ones they tend to issue warnings on and attempt to code out. <br>
<br>
I am sure SOE did not intend to make this work around for getting keyed. Though from what I am seeing, they are not in a rush to stop it either. Then again, who knows, new content means people stay longer.  It wouldn't shock me to see SOE make the doors to these places easier to open much like they did with the planes. <br>
<br>
I can also understand how a person that worked for the key would be angry. Just remember, if you were keyed 6 months ago, you are STILL better equipped then the guy that got keyed today.  <br>
<br>
Last thing. Don't judge a person or their knowledge based upon the level of their FV character. The majority of people have chars on many servers. Don't fool yourself into thinking because a person is level 30 here, they don't have a 65 elsewhere. <br>
<br>
Back to Ermok and his comments. He should be a posterchild for Uber Guilds and they way MANY (no not all) of their members think.  Sorry, but I have yet to have anyone convince me they are 'better' then me or 'above' me in EQ.  Games are for fun, if you gotta try to make yourself above others in what is a game made for entertainment, you have some serious self respect issues. <br>
